'''Transparency Options''' allow you to change the opacity of buildings and other map features. Each transparency option can be toggled by clicking on its specific button or using <code>ctrl</code> + (<code>1</code> to <code>9</code>). All [[en/Manual/Transparency options#locked-transparency-options|unlocked transparency options]] can be quicky toggled on/off by pressing <code>X</code>. Invisibility can be toggled by clicking on the button below the first row, or by using <code>shift</code>+<code>ctrl</code>+(<code>1</code> to <code>9</code>)

==Transparency Options Toolbar==
[[File:en/TransparencyOptions.png?]]
The Transparency Options toolbar has two rows:
*The first row defines what map feature is affected, and if it is locked.
*The second row defines what map feature should be invisible ''or'' transparent when the first row is set.

